      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROAD TO FAME (1) produced a modest effort most recently when seventh at Wentworth Park over 520m behind Dennis Keeping (30.79) in a Grade 5. Comes through a solid form race last start. Tough to beat if on-song. LAGNICOURT (7) flew the lids with a strong early split and led throughout to score an impressive win by 2.5 lengths over 400m at The Gardens (23.16). Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. MAGIC WYLDE (3) was among the minors three back at this track then missed the frame the last two, but drawn box 3 this time where he has two wins. Has the ability and expected to do much better. SHIFTY SHILOH (5) continues to race well and is sure to be competitive again.",
